parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Shift
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or failure to shift can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to lose power or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of transmission components can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, stalling, or difficulty controlling the vehicle.
Transmission performance issues can cause the vehicle to hesitate, stumble, or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Transmission drags down when the A/C is turned on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly maintain the transmission can lead to premature wear and tear, causing transmission problems.
symptoms: Transmission gasket needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lock up, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Crankwalk, a specific issue with the thrust bearing, can cause the motor to spin rod bearings, leading to engine failure.
symptoms: excessive oil consumption (2-3 quarts every 500 miles)

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing belt failure can cause major engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Engine stalling and surging can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Engine fires can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the driver and passengers.
The failure of the seat belt restraint system can lead to inadequate protection in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to restrain the driver or passenger during an accident
the seat belt retractor fails to retract
the seat belt becomes stuck halfway
the automatic shoulder restraint only works intermittently.
